      • QUERY_PROCESS_AREA

        static final java.lang.String QUERY_PROCESS_AREA
        The supported feed service query parameter name specifying the UUID identifier for the process area to query ChangeEvents for. Legal values for this parameter are defined as UUID.getUuidValue(), as available from IItemHandle.getItemId().

        This parameter may be present in the query string in the URI of the feed service, and is provided here as a possible key value in the map returned by IFeedFactory#getFeedParameters().

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • QUERY_FEEDTYPE

        static final java.lang.String QUERY_FEEDTYPE
        The supported feed service query parameter name specifying the type of the requested feed.

        This parameter may be present in the query string in the URI of the feed service, and is provided here as a possible key value in the map returned by IFeedFactory#getFeedParameters().

        See Also:

      • QUERY_FEED_PROVIDER

        static final java.lang.String QUERY_FEED_PROVIDER

      • QUERY_USER

        static final java.lang.String QUERY_USER
        The supported feed service query parameter name specifying the username to query ChangeEvents for (as the value of IContributor.getName() associated to the contributor that appears in either the author or contributor fields of the ChangeEvent). Specifying this field as a query parameter is equivalent to specifying both the QUERY_AUTHOR and QUERY_CONTRIBUTOR fields.

        This parameter may be present in the query string in the URI of the feed service, and is provided here as a possible key value in the map returned by IFeedFactory#getFeedParameters().

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • QUERY_AUTHOR

        static final java.lang.String QUERY_AUTHOR
        The supported feed service query parameter name specifying the username to query ChangeEvents for (as the value of IContributor.getName() associated to the author field of the ChangeEvent.

        This parameter may be present in the query string in the URI of the feed service, and is provided here as a possible key value in the map returned by IFeedFactory#getFeedParameters().

        See Also:

      • QUERY_CONTRIBUTOR

        static final java.lang.String QUERY_CONTRIBUTOR
        The supported feed service query parameter name specifying the username to query ChangeEvents for (as the value of IContributor.getName() associated to the contributors field of the ChangeEvent.

        This parameter may be present in the query string in the URI of the feed service, and is provided here as a possible key value in the map returned by IFeedFactory#getFeedParameters().

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • QUERY_SINCE

        static final java.lang.String QUERY_SINCE
        The supported feed service query parameter specifying the time to query ChangeEvents against. If specified, the value of IChangeEvent.getTime() is compared against this value. Only ChangeEvents whose time is equal to, or more recent than the specified value are returned. If specified, this value must be in ISO8601 format. See FeedUtils#getISO8601DateFormat().

        This parameter may be present in the query string in the URI of the feed service, and is provided here as a possible key value in the map returned by IFeedFactory#getFeedParameters().

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • QUERY_CATEGORY

        static final java.lang.String QUERY_CATEGORY
        The supported feed service query parameter name specifying the category to query ChangeEvents for (as found in the category field of the ChangeEvent).

        This parameter may be present in the query string in the URI of the feed service, and is provided here as a possible key value in the map returned by IFeedFactory#getFeedParameters().
